definition.value: A heparan sulfate composed of a backbone of repeating beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->4)-N-sulfonyl-alpha-D-glucosamine units joined by (1->4)-linkages.
An sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine substituted at the 1-oxygen by an alk-1-enyl group.
Any of a group of aminoglycoside antibiotics produced by fermentation of some Micromonospora spp.
